[SN]TITLE[SN]
Lorry fire and four-vehicle crash cause delays on A470

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A lorry fire and a four-vehicle crash have caused "severe delays" on the A470 in south Wales.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The southbound carriageway is closed at Merthyr Tydfil after a lorry caught fire between the Rhydycar roundabout and Abercanaid roundabout on Tuesday.
The four-vehicle accident happened on the northbound carriageway between Rhydyfelin and Pontypridd, with three casualties.
Both incidents were reported just before 17:00 GMT.
A South Wales Fire and Rescue Service spokesman said a crew from Whitchurch attended the crash and three people were treated by paramedics.
